abstract: Haru Nomura of Japan takes her first LPGA tournament by winning Women's Australian Open by three strokes; other golf news.
lead_paragraph: The Honolulu-based Haru Nomura of Japan won her first L.P.G.A. tournament in her 72nd start, shooting a closing seven-under-par 65 to win the Women’s Australian Open by three strokes in Adelaide.

headline.print_headline: Japanese Claims Her First L.P.G.A. Tournament
